cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper is about federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of wireless communication and non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA), which are related to networking and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. The paper also proposes a scheme to reduce aggregation latency, which is related to control systems and optimization. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category. Finally, the paper uses simulation to evaluate the proposed scheme, which is related to multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely but still possible category.
